gles\nwhich can double the SNR compared to a non-time-encoded protocol. The shortened\ntime-encoded readout can also lead to improved background suppression, reducing\nphysiological noise and further improving SNR.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 Apr 2022 19:01:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-05"}
